\title{Definitions of connectedness}
\date{2023-09-04}
\author{Ayberk Tosun}

\p{
  There are different definitions of connectedness that are classicaly
  equivalent.
}

\p{
  The [standard definition](axt-000E) is the one that says a space is connected
  if no separation for it exists.
}

\transclude{axt-000E}


\p{
  Another one is the nonexistence of nontrivial clopen sets.
}

\transclude{axt-000F}

These two definitions are classically equivalent.

\transclude{axt-000H}
